cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.AR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with differentiable neural architecture search, which is a popular topic in machine learning and falls under the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The paper also focuses on optimizing network latency, which is a key factor in computer vision and image processing, making "cs.CV" (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) another likely sub-category. The use of a multi-layer regressor for latency prediction and the evaluation of architectures on hardware suggest the involvement of artificial intelligence techniques, leading to "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) as another possible sub-category. The paper also deals with the optimization of non-differentiable factors such as power consumption, which falls under "cs.AR" (Hardware Architecture) and "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
